body:
Thanks, Kristof and Stefan! Really appreciate it.

@Stefaanhess: If you're having a look anyways, I think there's a bug in the `Trainer` state restoration: [This line](https://github.com/atomistic-machine-learning/schnetpack/blob/cd8bc502323a0f3c785dba8a3efe4eaae0002686/src/schnetpack/train/trainer.py#L114) should be using `state_dict` instead of `self.state_dict`, otherwise the hook state gets lost on recovery. :) 

This fix, and adding `best_loss` to the `EarlyStoppingHook` `state_dict` mostly fix the restart problem for me: now the `Trainer` runs for just one epoch.
